28/02/2008
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Serge Brammertz, the new chief prosecutor of The Hague war crimes tribunal, kicks off a two-day visit to Croatia on Thursday (February 28th) and will return to the Balkans next month.
Spokesperson Olga Kavran says he will be back to visit Sarajevo on March 6th.
Brammertz assumed his post on January 1st, succeeding Carla del Ponte.
(HRT - 28/02/08;
AFP, AP - 27/02/08)
